<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1002,1700]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,416,1002,1028]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Remarks on transfer</emphasis>
: Based on the leg spine formula, the position of the trichobothrium on the tibiae, the raised caput and the configuration of the male palp, the species is transferred from 
<emphasis box="[1191,1402,1040,1065]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Trachelocomptus</emphasis>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1884" box="[151,296,1077,1102]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Erigonoplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,296,1077,1102]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Erigonoplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1002,1700]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,353,1114,1140]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Description:</emphasis>
Measurements: Male: Total length 1.7; prosoma 0.72–0.84 long, 0.51–0.54 wide. Colour: Prosoma reddish brown, thoracic part yellowish brown; legs yellowish orange, patellae tinged with grey; abdomen grey. Male prosoma (
<figureCitation box="[529,618,1189,1215]" captionStart="FIGURES 43–56" captionStartId="25.[151,269,1778,1802]" captionText="FIGURES 43–56. Figs 43–46. Erigonoplus nasutus (O.P.-Cambridge, 1875); 43. Male prosoma, lateral view; 44. Male palp, prolateral view; 45. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 46. Embolic division, anteroventral view. Figs 47–49. Maso douro Bosmans &amp; Cardoso new species; 47. Male palp, prolateral view, with denticulate hairs in detail; 48. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 49. Embolic division, anterior view. Figs 50-56. Mecopisthes crassirostris (Simon, 1884); 50. Male prosoma, lateral view; 51. Idem, dorsal view; 52. Male palp, prolateral view; 53. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 54. Embolic division, anteroventral view; 55. Epigynum, ventral view; 56. Vulva, ventral view (E = embolus; StA = suprategular apophysis; Tp = tailpiece)." pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
) with large tubercle anteriorly protruded into a curved, hairy cone, dilating distally, with PM at lateral side of cone. Eyes: a = 0.75, b = 2.5, c = d = 1.75. Chelicerae: With 6, welldeveloped oblique stridulating grooves; 4 promarginal and 4 retromarginal teeth in fang groove. Legs: Typical row of ventral femoral spines not observed; spine formula 0011 (or spines in TI I–II broken off); L Sp Ti III– IV = 1; Tb Mt I = 0.43; Tb Mt IV absent. Palp (
<figureCitation box="[745,890,1338,1364]" captionStart="FIGURES 43–56" captionStartId="25.[151,269,1778,1802]" captionText="FIGURES 43–56. Figs 43–46. Erigonoplus nasutus (O.P.-Cambridge, 1875); 43. Male prosoma, lateral view; 44. Male palp, prolateral view; 45. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 46. Embolic division, anteroventral view. Figs 47–49. Maso douro Bosmans &amp; Cardoso new species; 47. Male palp, prolateral view, with denticulate hairs in detail; 48. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 49. Embolic division, anterior view. Figs 50-56. Mecopisthes crassirostris (Simon, 1884); 50. Male prosoma, lateral view; 51. Idem, dorsal view; 52. Male palp, prolateral view; 53. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 54. Embolic division, anteroventral view; 55. Epigynum, ventral view; 56. Vulva, ventral view (E = embolus; StA = suprategular apophysis; Tp = tailpiece)." pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Figs 44–46</figureCitation>
): Tibia with strongly elongated anterodorsal apophysis and with some strong retrolateral spines; paracymbium with broad basal and distal branches, distal branch with one strong spine; embolus with terminal and subterminal teeth.
</paragraph>
